\par\par \b \uc2  BI's benchmark interest rate drops to 17.15 percent. \b0\par\par\uc2 644 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 July 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The benchmark interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month promissory notes (SBI) fell by over 150-basis points to 17.15 percent at the weekly Wednesday auction, from 18.84 percent last week. \par \par \uc2  According to a \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  statement, the decline in the benchmark rate was in line with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's plans to continue relaxing monetary conditions over the next few months, with the hope of seeing the rate fall to below 15 percent at year-end. \par \par \uc2  "The improving monetary condition is expected to provide positive sentiment to the process of sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery," the statement said. \par \par \uc2  Separately, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Syahril Sabirin said at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) on Wednesday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would allow a further drop in \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the back of expectations of low inflation and a stronger rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "We expect inflation to remain low this month," he said after meeting with a group of legislators. \par \par \uc2  Inflation in June was negative 0.34 percent, the fourth consecutive deflation in four months. \par \par \uc2  But President B.J. Habibie seemed impatient to see the lower rates translated into cheaper credits to businesses. \par \par \uc2  "The President has instructed the finance minister to study why bank lending rates remain so high," Minister of Information Muhammad Yunus said after a limited Cabinet meeting on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Bank lending \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are currently hovering at about 30 percent. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said domestic banks need more time to adjust their lending rates to the current lower interest rate environment. \par \par \uc2  They also said banks could not be expected to resume significant lending in the near future, as banks were only now recovering from the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  onslaught. \par \par \uc2  Syahril was confident that inflation for the whole year would be in the single digits, lower than earlier projections of between 10 percent to 13 percent. \par \par \uc2  He emphasized the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's previous tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the stronger rupiah, production capacity availability, and the smooth distribution of goods as factors that would help push inflation down to the new target. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund (IMF) advised the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  last year to tighten monetary conditions in order to curb inflation and shore up the rupiah. The benchmark interest rate soared to more than 70 percent last August, when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis heightened. \par \par \uc2  Although the tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  sent many companies into bankruptcy and caused banks to suffer negative interest rate spread, inflation fell by only 2.73 percent in the first six months of the year. \par \par \uc2  Last year saw hyperinflation of 77.63 percent. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah also managed to strengthen to Rp 6,700 per U.S. dollar, compared to more than Rp 14,000 last year. \par \par \uc2  Syahril said positive developments in monetary conditions, coupled with a stable political condition, would provide a strong basis for the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  The government is projecting gross domestic product growth of between zero percent and 2 percent this year, compared to an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  contraction of 13.68 percent last year. \par \par \uc2  Businessmen have welcomed the declining trend in domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , saying they hoped banks would resume lending at affordable rates in the near future. \par \par \uc2  But some analysts warn that a drastic decline in domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would harm the exchange rate of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar, particularly in view of looming political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the run up to the presidential election. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed slightly lower on Wednesday at Rp 6,753 per dollar, from Rp 6,712 on Tuesday, in thin trade. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said the weakening of the rupiah was not due to the interest rate reduction, because the market often heard \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  official pronouncements of lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Syahril has repeatedly said a fair market range for the rupiah is between Rp 6,000 to Rp 6,500. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv7800aj5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
