\par\par \b \uc2  Pressure mounts to delay CGI donors meeting. \b0\par\par\uc2 726 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 July 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Pressure on the government and the World Bank to delay the upcoming donors meeting, which will provide the country with a new loan commitment, is mounting, with the National Mandate Party (PAN) jumping on the bandwagon. \par \par \uc2  PAN's head of international relations department Bara Hasibuan said on Saturday the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) donors meeting should be delayed until a new government resulting from the recent elections was formed. \par \par \uc2  "The transitional administration of President B.J. Habibie will soon end its term, so it doesn't have the right to make negotiations with foreigners, especially on matters which are fundamental and affect the lives of many people," he said. \par \par \uc2  Bara said PAN was also extremely concerned about the ability of Habibie's administration to manage foreign aid. He drew attention to the significant abuse of the multibillion dollar social safety net funds and other leakages. \par \par \uc2  "We urge donors grouped in the CGI to also respect the people's choice as reflected from the (provisional) elections result. The CGI must stop providing aid to the Habibie administration." \par \par \uc2  He said the National Awakening Party (PKB) and several non-governmental organizations grouped under INFID (the International NGO Forum on Indonesian Development) had joined forces with PAN in the hope of delaying the CGI meeting. \par \par \uc2  Bara said the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan) had yet to make a \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  statement on the issue. \par \par \uc2  "We plan to hold meetings with the World Bank and other donors to negotiate the delay." \par \par \uc2  The CGI meeting is scheduled to convene in Paris on July 27 and July 28 to decide on a new loan commitment for the country. \par \par \uc2  Deputy for international cooperation at the National Development Planning Board (Bappenas) Budhy Tjahjati said on Friday that multilateral and bilateral donors had indicated they would provide some US$5 billion in loans. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia received about $7.9 billion in aid from CGI last year. \par \par \uc2  INFID had earlier called for a delay of the CGI meeting until the formation of the country's new government. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia held its landmark elections on June 7. The popular opposition party, PDI Perjuangan, has been leading in provisional election results. \par \par \uc2  The 500-member \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  will join 200 provincial and community appointees to form the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body, the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR). In November, the MPR is scheduled to elect a president and vice president. \par \par \uc2  Separately, chairman of Bappenas Boediono said on Saturday the government and the World Bank, which chairs the CGI, would proceed with the donors meeting, despite intensifying demands for its postponement. \par \par \uc2  Boediono said the CGI meeting was crucial for the country to obtain donors confirmation to finance the current 1998/1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  gap, as well as a commitment for the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \uc2  "The main intention of the CGI meeting is to obtain confirmation for financing the current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . So it's not only for the (sake of) the current government, but also for the next new government. \par \par \uc2  "You can imagine how difficult it would be for a new government to negotiate such critical overseas loans," he said. \par \par \uc2  The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will end on March 31, 1999, while a new government is expected to be formed later this year. \par \par \uc2  Boediono declined to specify the loan amount needed from CGI, but it has been projected the country would need some $1.9 billion. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia needs $10.3 billion in overseas funds to finance the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Most of the foreign aid requirement has so far been fulfilled. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, AFP reported that Japan would send a working-level delegation to Indonesia on Monday for talks on aid to Indonesia, ahead of the CGI meeting. \par \par \uc2  The delegation, including a senior finance ministry official, will discuss specific aid projects in the hope of rebuilding the battered Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  A ministry official said Tokyo viewed the upcoming Paris meeting as "a place where the international community will express their confidence in Indonesia" following the general election. \par \par \uc2  But it remained \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  whether the Paris meeting would agree to provide a large sum of aid to Indonesia, AFP said. \par \par \uc2  The agency said concerns had been expressed on the part of the United States and European donor nations about the new Indonesian government and allegations of misuse of foreign aid. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv7c00ari\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
