\par\par \b \uc2  Expert sees quick recovery in prime condominium market. \b0\par\par\uc2 521 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 July 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): A property consultancy firm predicted on Monday demand for prime condominiums in Jakarta would recover sooner than expected given the country's continuing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  improvement. \par \par \uc2  PT Procon Indah/Jones Lang LaSalle said buyers' confidence had begun to recover at the end of the second quarter of 1999 following improvements in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the strengthening of the rupiah and the peaceful general election. \par \par \uc2  "Individual investors consider residential property as part of their investment portfolio due to banks' declining \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the (country's) expected political and social stability," the company said in its biweekly report. \par \par \uc2  However, the company said sales of middle to lower-priced condominiums would likely remain quiet until mortgage availability and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  returned to precrisis levels. \par \par \uc2  The company also said prices quoted in rupiah for prime and middle to lower-priced condominiums would maintain their decline due to the rupiah's expected continued strengthening against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  "We may see prices of prime condominiums stabilize in early 2000. For middle to lower-priced condominiums, prices are expected to increase in early 2001 when demand has improved," the company said. \par \par \uc2  Average condominium prices in rupiah declined 12.8 percent to Rp 5.12 million per square meter in prime residential locations over the first quarter of 1999. Prices declined by 8.8 percent to Rp 8.3 million per square meter in Jakarta's central business district (CBD). \par \par \uc2  Condominium prices quoted in U.S dollars fluctuated depending on the exchange rate of the rupiah against the dollar. Average prices in dollar terms declined by 19 percent in prime residential locations and 15 percent in the CBD in the first quarter of the year. \par \par \uc2  The company said condominium sales remained quiet in the first half of 1999 due to political and social \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the general election. \par \par \uc2  However, the number of prospective buyers increased significantly in mid-June, with the elections being free of the much-feared violence. Most prospective buyers were in the market for prime condominiums for primary home or investment purposes, either in the primary or secondary market. \par \par \uc2  The total number of condominiums stood at 22,958 units as of March 1999, a 0.9 percent increase from last year, according to the report. \par \par \uc2  The first-quarter increase in condominiums was the result of the completion of construction on the 131-unit Menara Matahari Condominium in Karawaci, Tanggerang, and the 67-unit Gunung Sahari Apartments in North Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Another project, the 52-unit Sailendra Apartment in Mega Kuningan, was completed in May 1999. \par \par \uc2  Several condominium projects were resumed in mid-June after being temporarily halted during the elections. \par \par \uc2  Completion of the projects is likely to be at least six months late due to the construction delay. \par \par \uc2  Construction of 4,656 units is currently under way, with construction scheduled to be completed by the end of 2001. \par \par \uc2  Construction of two 1,587-unit condominium projects in Kelapa Gading, North Jakarta, and Permata Hijau, South Jakarta, has been delayed since the beginning of 1999, the report said. (gis) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv7d00au1\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Parliament agrees CGI meeting to go on as scheduled. \b0\par\par\uc2 346 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 July 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The parliament and the government agreed that the Consultative Group for Indonesia (CGI) meeting should go on as scheduled in order to get a certainty on the financing resources for the 1999/2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' Commission VIII agreed that the meeting be held on 27-28 July 1999," said Johny Alwi Banyo, chairman of the meeting between Commission VIII and Head of the National Board for Development Planning (Bappenas) Boediono yesterday. \par \par \uc2  In its conclusion, the parliament also asked the Head of the National Board for Development Planning to include the parliament in any agreements made regarding foreign loans. \par \par \uc2  Bappenas Head Boediono on that occasion reminded on the importance why the meeting should be held on 27-28 July 1999, which is to secure financing for the 1999/2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  According to Boediono, if the financing of the 1999/2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  ended until the current government, it will only create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the market. "The market will be wondering why there is a big hole in this year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , this issue will only bring disadvantage to us all," said Boediono. \par \par \uc2  Boediono hoped that the political transition will not hamper the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  pick-up. "We have to learn how to make sure that the political changes won't hurt the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , that's all," he said. \par \par \uc2  The current government will be able to confirm the financial resources for the 1999/2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the CGI meeting. "We would already have the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and would be legalized by the parliament. We will try to secure the financing," said Boediono. \par \par \uc2  According to Boediono, the 27-28 July 1999 CGI meeting will be good for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the impact can only be seen after three months and this will cover the financial needs until March 2000. \par \par \uc2  "This means, if we have it [CGI meeting] in July 1999, it will cover until March next year. Think how good will it be for our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. (msw). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dv7e0018b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
