\par\par \b \uc2  Condition of local banks still fragile, senior analyst says. \b0\par\par\uc2 885 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 July 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Some of the 74 A-category banks which had a relatively stronger capital condition early in the year have now suffered either a negative or insufficient capital adequacy ratio (CAR) due to a continuing "negative environment," said a senior banking analyst. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto Sastroatmodjo said on Friday that the CAR level of about half of the 74 banks might have already dropped to below the minimum 4 percent level requirement. \par \par \uc2  "The fate of this group of banks is still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and very fragile amid the (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) condition which remains unable to provide a positive support for their operation," he told a seminar on the prospects of national banks. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto said the banks would either have to merge themselves or have their owners inject fresh money to help the banks stay afloat. \par \par \uc2  He added that the group of banks could not yet be expected to resume lending to the real sector. \par \par \uc2  A-category banks are privately owned banks which do not have to join the government's bank recapitalization program because they had a CAR level of more than 4 percent. The banks had an average CAR level of more than 10 percent when their status was announced in March this year. \par \par \uc2  CAR is the ratio between equity capital and risk-weighted assets. \par \par \uc2  The government closed 38 private banks with a CAR level of less than minus 25 percent in March, and decided to recapitalize nine banks which had a CAR level between minus 25 percent and plus 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto said the CAR condition of the A-category banks continued to deteriorate since the announcement of their status in March due to the negative interest rate spread problem that plagued the industry for many months amid the high interest rate environment. \par \par \uc2  Most of the country's banks have put their funds on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's short-term promissory notes (SBIs) to reduce lending risks. But this has caused a negative spread to their interest earning position as the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  of their time deposits are much lower than the rates offered by the SBIs. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto said although \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  had now gone down sharply to levels which should provide banks with a positive spread, the A-category banks remained in difficulty as they were plagued with huge non-performing loans (NPLs). \par \par \uc2  He said that unlike the NPLs of the recapitalized banks or nationalized banks, those of the A-category banks were not transferred to the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  "IBRA doesn't bail out the NPLs of the A-category banks," Rijanto said. \par \par \uc2  IBRA is expected to absorb more than Rp 230 trillion in NPLs from seven private banks, seven state banks and 13 nationalized banks, all of which would be recapitalized by the government to allow them to have a clean balance sheet and to resume lending once they were recapitalized. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto said it would be impossible to expect the A-category banks to resume lending over the next six to 12 months. \par \par \uc2  "These banks can't be expected to resume lending except on program loans," he said, referring to the heavily subsidized government loans which are channeled through a selected group of banks. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has allowed its benchmark interest rate to drop significantly from more than 35 percent in the beginning of this year to a current level of 13.80 percent, in the hope to push down the bank lending rate to an affordable level for the real sector. \par \par \uc2  State banks have almost completely stopped lending to the real sector since last year when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  fell deeper into its worst \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in three decades. \par \par \uc2  In its latest Memorandum of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Financial Policies (MEFP) to the International Monetary Fund (IMF), the government said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) was expected to complete an evaluation of the 74 A-category banks by July 31. \par \par \uc2  "By that date, it is envisaged that all owners, managers and directors of these banks who failed the fit and proper test will be removed, and former controlling shareholders who failed the test will fully divest their holdings," the MEFP document said. \par \par \uc2  It also said that by July 31, BI would also complete its review and discussion of an individual bank's financial soundness and business plan. \par \par \uc2  It added that corrective programs to deal with unviable business plans would be established, where necessary, with individual banks by September 30. \par \par \uc2  "Through this process, and regular supervision, BI will ensure that private banks remain solvent," the document said. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto also said that many of the foreign joint venture banks operating in the country were facing a similar fate as the A-category banks. \par \par \uc2  "Several joint venture banks also have the same problem," he said, adding their local partners were in financial difficulties to provide their share of fresh money to increase the CAR level. \par \par \uc2  Based on the December 1998 due diligence audit conducted by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , out of 32 joint-venture banks in Indonesia, 15 banks posted a CAR level of equal or more than 4 percent, and 17 banks had a CAR level below 4 percent. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  closed down two joint-venture banks including Bank Indovest and Bank LTCB in April because their owners failed to recapitalize the banks. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv7v0070z\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  ' \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  recovery faces problems'. \b0\par\par\uc2 173 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 July 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Many factors could upset \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, including the government's sense of complacency on signs of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery that could potentially impede reforms. \par \par \uc2  The body noted that \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  abounds over increased production, consumption and investment, three elements that are required for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  "There is also the problem of complacency, which could impede crucial reforms, especially in banking and corporate restructuring," said Oliver Draper of Strategic Intelligence here yesterday, on the eve of a conference on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects 25 August. \par \par \uc2  Draper noted that the current source of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  supported by the IMF and the World Bank. \par \par \uc2  To sustain that growth, he added, "domestic demand and exports must rise, none of which have yet shown signs of recovery." \par \par \uc2  "The IMF is still needed to ensure that current reforms would continue." \par \par \uc2  "This requires patience as there are pressures to speed up or to seek short-term popular solutions which could have a negative impact on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as a whole." (ab). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dv7v001b4\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'Recovery depends on settlement of bad loans'. \b0\par\par\uc2 281 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 August 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Indonesian chamber of commerce and industry (Kadin) chief said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could grow faster next year if bad loans of 200 large debtors under BPPN could be settled by the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  Kadin general chairman Aburizal Bakrie [Ical] said here last week that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth does not need to wait for "a 100% private debt settlement." \par \par \uc2  In the letter of intent (LOI) to the IMF on 22 July, BPPN disclosed that at least 784 debtors - including 200 large debtors-have signed letters of commitment (LOC). Those who refused will have their names publicly disclosed on 31 August. \par \par \uc2  They will also be imposed with sanctions, one of which being declard bankrupt one month after the announcement. \par \par \uc2  Ical also said the business world is still facing problems due to high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , despite currrent SBI rates at 13,5% and the ample availability of funds. \par \par \uc2  Banking, Ical said, still needs time for consolidation before making loans to the real sector as SBI rates had gone down from 30% to 13.5% within one month. \par \par \uc2  "On the other hand, they still carry the burden of paying 30% rates," he added. \par \par \uc2  "Credits to the real sector may start in August or September." \par \par \uc2  However, Ical added, the business world needs political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and that it hopes the presidential election in November will proceed smoothly. \par \par \uc2  On the performance of BPPN, Ical said it is working hard to restructure corporate debt but he wished it would work faster in dealing with the 2,000 companies. \par \par \uc2  Ical added, however, "the more companies that could be saved, the more debts that could be recovered." (ens). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dv82001be\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
