\par\par \b \uc2  Reformist parties urged to share an  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  platform. \b0\par\par\uc2 590 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 August 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Noted economist Emil Salim urged a trio of major "reformist" political parties on Tuesday to form a common \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  platform to help solve the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems. \par \par \uc2  Emil said that the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan), the National Awakening Party (PKB) and the National Mandate Party (PAN) should create the shared platform as a guideline for a new coalition government. \par \par \uc2  "Since PDI Perjuangan led in the (June 7) elections, it should be the one who's proactive in talking to PKB and PAN," he told a seminar on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  platforms of the three political parties. It was organized by prestigious think tank the Center for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS). \par \par \uc2  He described it as a realistic suggestion since the major \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs of the three parties were mostly similar. \par \par \uc2  Emil, one of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  architects during the golden era of the ruling Golkar Party, noted the three parties were not against the market \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The three also consider the important role of the government to provide a level playing field for the business sector, and are committed to developing provincial economies," said the U.S.-trained economist. \par \par \uc2  PDI Perjuangan, PKB and PAN, part of the country's top five political parties, are regarded as the true reformist parties and the most serious challengers to the long rule of the Golkar Party, the political vehicle of the Soeharto government. \par \par \uc2  Although PDI-P won 33.7 percent of the June \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  elections, the party did not gain enough votes to form a single-majority government. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the next leadership has fanned increasing calls for the three parties to form a coalition and shut out a the possible return of Golkar to power. \par \par \uc2  Economists from the three reformist political parties welcome Emil's suggestion. \par \par \uc2  "The suggestion of Pak Emil is not something impossible to realize," said S.G.B. Tampubolon, a PDI Perjuangan \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  adviser. \par \par \uc2  "Three heads are better than one." \par \par \uc2  He said that he would recommend that his party immediately hold discussions with the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  teams of PKB and PAN. \par \par \uc2  "But I'm not in a capacity to answer the question whether we're going to form a coalition, although I personally believe that it would be a good thing because who else could we talk to?" \par \par \uc2  Yusuf Faishal, head of PKB's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  department, agreed that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs proposed by the three parties were relatively similar. \par \par \uc2  After speaking in seminars with economists from the other two parties in recent months, he noted a seeming convergence in their programs. \par \par \uc2  "It's no longer clear who's duplicating whose programs," he said. \par \par \uc2  PAN secretary-general Faisal Basri said that the prospect of forming a common \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  platform was strong enough because the country's major political parties often met to discuss various issues. \par \par \uc2  The country has been battered by the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis which started in July 1997. The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  contracted by 13.68 percent last year, putting millions of people out of work and increasing the number of Indonesians living below the poverty line. \par \par \uc2  The government adopted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs sponsored by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) in an effort to right its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems. \par \par \uc2  Several economists have said a new government might demand the tough \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs be renegotiated with the IMF. \par \par \uc2  The presidential election is scheduled for November. PDI Perjuangan chairwoman Megawati Sukarnoputri and incumbent President B.J. Habibie, who is supported by Golkar, are the leading contenders. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv840075n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
