\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty \highlight\uc2  crippling  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 727 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 September 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Indonesian government once again demonstrated its determination to cover up corruption in the highest levels by invoking the banking secrecy law as a legal pretext for not fully disclosing the results of the PricewaterhouseCoopers audit of the transactions relating to the Bank Bali scandal. A similar excuse was used in June to protect former attorney general Andi M. Ghalib from prosecution on allegations of corruption. \par \par \uc2  The government's stubborn refusal to lay bare all the pertinent facts of the Rp 546 billion (around US$80 million) scandal, despite the relentless demand for full disclosure from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , all those concerned by a seemingly pervasive abuse of power and multilateral creditors, simply reflects its total disregard of the principles of morality, ethics, transparency and accountability. \par \par \uc2  This scandal negates all the official campaigns and new laws against corruption, collusion and nepotism, and makes it imperative to move forward the presidential election from mid-November to early October in order to replace the Habibie administration. The longer Habibie retains the presidency, the greater the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and tension, which is already crippling the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , will grow. \par \par \uc2  One should not be so surprised by the highly orchestrated attempt to cover up and reduce the magnitude of the scandal, which, according to the findings of the independent auditor, involved House members, senior \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political party officials and members of President B.J. Habibie's inner circle. \par \par \uc2  But given the devastating impact of the high-profile case on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and on investor and creditor confidence in the country, it is alarming to see how Habibie has rashly employed all the tricks at his disposal to cling to power, without consideration to the damage done to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The refusal to fully disclose the audit results virtually nullifies the government's widely hailed move to appoint an independent auditor in the first place, admittedly a move it made only after some pressure from the International Monetary Fund. Indonesia may be the first country in the world willing to accept the indignity of allowing a foreign auditor to poke its nose into its \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the fortress of its monetary system. The nation was forced to suffer this humiliation because its government has such low credibility and integrity in the eyes of the international community. \par \par \uc2  Now the great sacrifice of appointing a foreigner auditor, a move aimed at regaining international confidence, is at risk of being wasted by the government's refusal to fully make \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  the findings of the audit. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has so far been true to its word that it would delay disbursing further aid to the country as long as this scandal remained unresolved, and the World Bank and the Asian Development Bank will surely follow in the IMF's steps. Though \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers attempted to play down the impact of the aid suspension, this punishment will surely hurt the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  because the three multilateral agencies account for about half of the $43 billion bailout of Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  And no amount of diplomacy will be effective in securing the release of the $23 billion portion of this bailout which was committed by government creditors. This money will be extended only after the portion pledged by the three multilateral institutions is disbursed. \par \par \uc2  The IMF and other multilateral institutions were not exaggerating when they warned last month of a disaster for Indonesia if the politically charged Bank Bali scandal was not properly resolved. Nor are they attempting to intervene in the country's internal affairs, for what really happened at Bank Bali was the daylight robbery of a huge sum of taxpayers' money at a time when millions of people have either lost their jobs or plunged below the poverty line because of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. Corruption, collusion and nepotism, the underlying causes of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , social and political crises here, are fully embodied in the Bank Bali scandal. \par \par \uc2  It is therefore most urgent now for the major reformist political parties to put aside their own interests and join forces to save the nation by accelerating the process of forming a credible government that values the principles of accountability and transparency. The longer this current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  prevails, the greater the damage to the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the more vulnerable the next government will be to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , social and political instability. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv9m0057t\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Standard and Poor's revises MPP's rate. \b0\par\par\uc2 490 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 September 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Standard and Poor's has revised rating of PT Matahari Putra Prima (MPP) to CC with implication of CreditWatch Developing from CC with negative implication (CreditWatch Negative) that was effective on 11 February 1998. \par \par \uc2  The rating company stated that the change is also imposed on the 11.25% notes worth US$100 million which matures on 15 March 2001, issued by Matahari International Finance Co BV and guaranteed by MPP. \par \par \uc2  The rating change shows that the business in Indonesia is \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  which is in line with Indonesia's weakening banking and financial performances. \par \par \uc2  Matahari with consumers from the medium to high social strata is dealing with an unpredictable trading condition and problems in getting loans. \par \par \uc2  According to S & P, the retail company also depends on the rupiah fluctuation while the loans and rent are dollar denominated. \par \par \uc2  Last year's performance had been slow due to the mass riots which caused problems in its distribution lines and closure of a number of outlets. \par \par \uc2  Political situation \par \par \uc2  The company's rating will be even lower should the political situation and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition during the presidential election this year worsens. \par \par \uc2  Such condition will affect the domestic retail operation and most likely create the same condition in 1998 where there was social unrest, said S & P. \par \par \uc2  For Matahari, based on S & P's observation, the factor that will support its business in the next few months is stability. \par \par \uc2  Stability will increase the level of consumers' expenditures and in turn result in a positive operation cash flow. \par \par \uc2  If that happens, the company will be able to meet its financial obligation and may lead to a rate upgrade. \par \par \uc2  S & P said the delayed short-term investment will improve the capital structure if the company uses its funds to pay loans. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the company in the first semester booked a net profit of Rp 130 billion in line with the Rp 40.8 billion interest gains. \par \par \uc2  When announcing the company's performance, President Director of the company Robert H Hacker said the company's improved performance took place in the second quarter due to increased productivity and efficiency. \par \par \uc2  According to him, there is an indication of increasing consumers \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  pattern in May and June 1999 which generated the same result as in 1997. \par \par \uc2  The company's sales value in the first semester of 1999 reached Rp 1.35 trillion or up 26% compared to the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  The operation profit reached Rp 74.1 billion or 5.5% from the total sales. The gross profit margin was 29.7% while last year's was 35.8%. \par \par \uc2  The company's strategy to reduce the size of stores, renting the remaining spaces and reducing costs resulted in the total operation cost of Rp 327.4 billion or 24.2% from sales, while last year it reached 34.3%, he said. (rn) \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dv9o0004l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
