\par\par \b \uc2  Investment banks to oversee BCA IPO. \b0\par\par\uc2 583 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 October 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) announced on Monday that it had appointed investment banks Lehman Brothers and Merrill Lynch and local securities firms PT Danareksa Sekuritas and PT Bahana Securities to prepare the initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering (IPO) for Bank Central Asia (BCA). \par \par \uc2  "The IPO will be made either at the end of this year or early next year, depending on the market condition," IBRA announced in a press statement. \par \par \uc2  The agency said it was determined to maximize the IPO proceeds to help finance the government bank restructuring program. \par \par \uc2  BCA, the country's largest private bank, was nationalized in August 1998, after the bank breached the legal lending limit and its owners, the Salim Group and former president Soeharto's children, failed to repay massive emergency liquidity support from the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  BCA had total assets of Rp 84.4 trillion (US$10.8 billion) and Rp 1.6 trillion in equity. As of June, BCA had some 767 branches throughout the country and 21,859 employees. \par \par \uc2  The government recapitalized the bank in May. \par \par \uc2  "IBRA is determined to develop and promote the Indonesian capital market. We're confident that the offering will restore confidence in the recovery of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said IBRA chairman Glenn S. Yusuf. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has a mission to help finance the government bank restructuring program, which is expected to cost some Rp 550 trillion, or roughly half of the country's gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  The government will issue bonds to finance the program. The government is expected to issue more than Rp 300 trillion worth of bonds this year mainly to finance the recapitalization cost of several major banks. \par \par \uc2  The total interest cost of the bonds in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year ending in March 2000 is estimated at Rp 34 trillion, half of which would be covered by the sale of IBRA assets, including BCA. \par \par \uc2  IBRA currently controls some Rp 600 trillion worth of assets and non-performing loans. \par \par \uc2  Many, however, have expressed doubts over whether IBRA can raise the targeted Rp 17 trillion of proceeds amid the country's political upheavals and the Bank Bali scandal which implicated two of the agency's deputy chairmen: Farid Harianto and Pande Lubis. \par \par \uc2  IBRA deputy chairman Arwin Rasyid acknowledged last week that if the political unrest dragged on till January, the agency would be unable to achieve the target. \par \par \uc2  Farid said that considering BCA's substantial size, the bank's IPO would be an acid test for the future of IBRA's asset disposal program. \par \par \uc2  "We hope this IPO will be successful," he said. \par \par \uc2  Sentiment toward Indonesia's stock market has been bearish amid the current political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , although some said that if the Oct. 20 presidential election unfolded smoothly, a bullish Jakarta Stock Exchange would follow. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Bambang Subianto expressed satisfaction over IBRA's handling of the BCA \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offer. \par \par \uc2  "The ability of IBRA in preparing BCA's \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering is very impressive. The government very much appreciates the progress which has been achieved and expects this success to also be extended to other bank recapitalization programs," Bambang said, in an apparent move to dismiss questions over IBRA professionalism. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has been under strong criticism over the Bank Bali scandal. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  special investigative team recently concluded that President B.J. Habibie should suspend several ministers and high-ranking government officials, including Bambang and Jusuf, over their indirect involvement in the scandal. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dva5005jb\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
