\par\par \b \uc2  Indonesianists give mixed views on Gus Dur's win. \b0\par\par\uc2 841 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 October 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): News of Abdurrahman Wahid's win in the presidential election met on Wednesday with mixed reactions among Indonesianists abroad with most expressing surprise and cautious optimism. \par \par \uc2  "If you had asked me five or six years ago whether Abdurrahman would be a good president, I would have said yes. But after his stroke, he became hard to follow. Nobody knows what he is going to do next," said Arief Budiman of the University of Melbourne in Australia. \par \par \uc2  Arief was pleased about one aspect: the victory of the reform movement. \par \par \uc2  He expressed hope that Abdurrahman would accommodate all sides in forming his Cabinet, including a coalition with the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan). \par \par \uc2  The possibility of widescale unrest is reduced by the fact that Abdurrahman is Megawati's good friend, so PDI Perjuangan supporters should not be too outraged, Arief said. \par \par \uc2  Richard W. Baker of the East West Center in Hawaii said the election of Abdurrahman as President was considered an unlikely outcome by many right up until the actual counting of the ballots. \par \par \uc2  However, he said that it had to be assessed as a profoundly positive development for Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman is the one figure who demonstrated an ability to work with virtually all the other contenders and factions, he said. \par \par \uc2  "The traits that have sometimes made him appear unpredictable, even inconsistent, in recent months may now enable him, as President, to bring together the widest possible political coalition." \par \par \uc2  "Abdurrahman's fundamental personal integrity, his resilience in which he withstood concerted efforts by the Soeharto government to undermine his position within Nahdlatul Ulama, started well before Megawati's trials as leader of the PDI, and his dedication to the creation of a more democratic, honest and clean government are beyond doubt." \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman also has substantial international experience and is widely respected around the world. These attributes should also serve him and Indonesia well in the difficult period of recovery that still lies ahead, he said. \par \par \uc2  "Abdurrahman's \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  health has been widely seen as his greatest liability as a candidate. However, it also provides additional assurance that as President he will focus on serving the nation's interests rather than enhancing and perpetuating his own position." \par \par \uc2  Nevertheless, the major \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about his presidency remains whether his health will permit him to govern energetically enough, and long enough, to bring about fundamental, enduring change in the government and political systems, he said. \par \par \uc2  In short, Baker said the election of Abdurrahman may well turn out to be a classic moment in Indonesian political history - a surprise outcome that has given the country the right leader, with the right combination of qualities, at a time when those qualities are sorely needed. \par \par \uc2  Harold Crouch of the Australian National University said, "I really thought that Abdurrahman would have pulled out in favor of Megawati." \par \par \uc2  Crouch described Abdurrahman as unpredictable and interesting. And he would not indulge in corruption, collusion and nepotism. \par \par \uc2  "Though whether he can deal with corruption, collusion, nepotism is another thing." \par \par \uc2  Whatever he would do, Crouch said, it would be different from what Habibie had done. Crouch's concern was his inclination to be erratic, which could cause continuous \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the political configuration of the country. \par \par \uc2  What Damien Kingsbury, the executive director of Monash Asia Institute, saw as advantageous was that Abdurrahman would be able to bring together an alliance of Islamic and reformist groups, such as the United Development Party (PPP) and the reformist faction of Golkar and PDI Perjuangan. \par \par \uc2  "Another leader would have been more divisive," said Kingsbury. \par \par \uc2  However, Kingsbury had some reservations about how quickly Abdurrahman shifted positions lately. \par \par \uc2  This, he said, might have a destabilizing effect in the future political configuration. \par \par \uc2  Kingsbury was also concerned about how Megawati's supporters would react to such a close defeat. \par \par \uc2  As for how stable the future government would be, Kingsbury believed it would depend on who Abdurrahman would appoint in his Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  Of no less importance, he said, was the person who would be the Indonesian Military chief. \par \par \uc2  "However, I believe Abdurrahman is a good consensus candidate. And that is a good thing," Kingsbury concluded. \par \par \uc2  Bob Lowry of the Australian Defense Academy in Canberra and author of The Armed Forces of Indonesia, also pointed to the fact that Abdurrahman was a democrat. "He's a reformist. Not one of the old guards," he said. \par \par \uc2  However, Lowry suspected that Abdurrahman may have done deals with some of the "old guards". \par \par \uc2  "It is interesting that Golkar did not run their candidate," he said. Lowry believed that the future government had an enormous challenge. \par \par \uc2  "They need to do a complete overhaul of the whole system. Reestablish the rule of law, review defense \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , review internal \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , promote \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and political stability. And they have to show some results pretty quickly. They must learn from the Pakistan lesson, where the military were driven to take over power because the civilian government had made such a mess of it." (hbk) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dval00647\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Despite volatility, RI offers largest investment increase in Asia. \b0\par\par\uc2 580 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 October 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Foreign investors said Indonesia has offered the largest share investment raise in Asia despite volatility for more time to come. \par \par \uc2  The market had earlier expected to see the most favorite candidate Megawati Sukarnoputri to be elected as the President. The market even strengthened by 10% or around 60 points and the rupiah went up 8% compared to Tuesday morning's trade in London. \par \par \uc2  But after Gus Dur's victory, gains at the bourse corrected from its highest position. The rupiah went lower to Rp 7,450 per dollar, compared to Rp 7,550 at Tuesday morning trade in London. The price of the Eurobond Indonesia which matures in tempo 2006 went up 630 basis points from the recent US Treasury Bills of 600. \par \par \uc2  "If you look at the preliminary market reactions on news over Habibie, you can see what could happen if Indonesia can solve its political problems," said Ashok Shah, Emerging Market Fund Manager Old Mutual as quoted by Reuters London. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , however, continues to loom. While on the other hand, prices of assets strengthen, in which strong rallies were seen since at the end of September after the currency suffered a correction of 17% in the third quarter and the stock market experienced a correction of 32% in dollar terms. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has rebounded from its recent position of Rp 8,800 per dollar, while the spread of Eurobond Indonesia in 2006 is down again to 600 basis points and the stock market improved from 515 to 584.425. \par \par \uc2  Although the spread of Eurobond has once again increased to 630 basis points from US Treasuries, traders said the activity was very thin. \par \par \uc2  "It will take a few sessions for Eurobond to find its balanced points," said one of the traders. \par \par \uc2  The situation, however, is still heated and volatile. The potential of political violence began when a bomb exploded at the Hotel Indonesia Circle after Megawati lost the presidential election. \par \par \uc2  Aside from those fears, what's important is Abdurrahman Wahid's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, said investors. Despite such condition, the level of the currency float and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's independence are still accepted by the market. Other issue is the military's role in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "We still don't know about its \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We are still waiting to see who the vice president is," said Mitul Kotecha, emerging market strategist Standard Chartered in London. \par \par \uc2  Key \par \par \uc2  The key now is if Gus Dur chooses the Defense Chief Wiranto as vice president, it will arouse anger from Megawati's supporters which will then develop into riots. \par \par \uc2  Whatever happens in Indonesia's political problems, some foreign investors with guts are positioning themselves in facing the rallies in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Tim Love, global emerging market strategist SG Securities recommended 2.4% portion for global equity fund in Indonesia, higher compared to the benchmark of International Finance Corporation Composite Index of 1.85%. \par \par \uc2  He predicts Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will see a 2.8% growth in 2000 after it was predicted to contract by 0.7% in 1999 and minus 16% in 1998. \par \par \uc2  If the reform continues to take place, mainly on politics, Indonesia will see some positive signs. Moreover the Bank Bali scandal report made by auditor PriceWaterhouseCoopers which will be publicly announced and the supports of the IMF and the US government will give a positive sign. "Indonesia is very risky, but has a high return," said Shah. (ind). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dval000e1\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
