\par\par \b \uc2  New govt told to set up New Order-free Cabinet. \b0\par\par\uc2 619 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 October 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Analysts called on the newly elected Abdurrahman Wahid-Megawati Soekarnoputri government on Thursday to establish a "New Order free" cabinet. \par \par \uc2  "I hope that there will be no element of the New Order (in the cabinet)," noted political analyst Soedjati Djiwandono told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Soedjati was referring to the much criticized government under former president Soeharto who resigned in May last year amid savage riots and mounting student protests. \par \par \uc2  "I hope that the next cabinet members will be younger and are not mere "yes men" people. They should be more independent and able to do more than just wait for instructions," Soedjati said. \par \par \uc2  He also said that Abdurrahman and Megawati would have to be able "to lead and to coordinate" the cabinet members. \par \par \uc2  The choice has heightened optimism that Abdurrahman and Megawati would be able to lead the country out of the current political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil. \par \par \uc2  Senior political analyst Mochtar Pabottingi shared Soedjati's view saying that the next cabinet must consist of proreform and competent members. \par \par \uc2  "The members must also be free from any corrupt practices," Mochtar said. \par \par \uc2  Speaker of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) Akbar Tandjung said on Thursday that Abdurrahman had been given a one-week deadline to set up the cabinet. \par \par \uc2  Leader of Abdurrahman's National Awakening Party (PKB) Alwi Shihab, however, was quoted by Antara as saying on Thursday that Abdurrahman would need up to two weeks to set up the new cabinet. \par \par \uc2  Golkar deputy chairman Marzuki Darusman said that the next cabinet should be "a national-based cabinet". \par \par \uc2  "It should be a national-based cabinet respecting the major sociopolitical forces, but it should be combined with expertise," Marzuki said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, political observer Arbi Sanit said the next cabinet should accommodate all elements in society. \par \par \uc2  "The next cabinet should accommodate political parties that have played a decisive role in the Assembly, including the axis force that nominated Abdurrahman in the presidential election," he said referring to a caucus of several Muslim-based parties in the Assembly. \par \par \uc2  Arbi said the cabinet should be simplified to promote efficiency amidst the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  "The cabinet should consist of between 20 and 25 ministers. State departments that are considered ineffective and inefficient should be disbanded while coordinating minister posts should be phased out," he said. \par \par \uc2  Habibie's Reform-Development took 38 people onboard comprising of four coordinating ministers, 20 ministers heading departments, 12 state ministers, the Attorney General and the Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Calls for a slimline cabinet also came from DPR deputy speaker Khofifah Indar Parawansa of the PKB. \par \par \uc2  Noted lawyer Todung Mulya Lubis stressed the need for the new leadership to establish a cabinet comprised of "professional" people as the country was facing serious problems. \par \par \uc2  "The next cabinet should contain professionals and should not recruit those who had been involved in the New Order government," he said. \par \par \uc2  Todung brushed aside suggestions that it was more important to satisfy the need for political seats in the cabinet, saying that including qualified people should be the central consideration. \par \par \uc2  "It is not important for the cabinet to be filled by politicians from political parties," he said. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman, before being elected president, told journalists on Monday that some ministries including Religious Affairs, Foreign and Education affairs may be filled from the PKB. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said some ministries may be filled from the axis force while a number of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials could come from Megawati's Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan). \par \par \uc2  Analysts also said Abdurrahman was likely to pick some members from the Golkar Party in return for the latter's support in the presidential election. (05/byg/emf/rms) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dvam00677\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
