\par\par \b \uc2  Morgan Stanley sees rupiah's value at 6,000 by year-end. \b0\par\par\uc2 554 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 October 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Indonesia's newly established legitimate government will boost the rupiah's value against the U.S. dollar toward 6,000 by year-end, according to an estimate by the United States-based investment bank Morgan Stanley Dean Witter (MWD). \par \par \uc2  "We see scope for the dollar-rupiah to trade toward Rp 6,000 by year-end," the investment bank said in its report. \par \par \uc2  It said that the currently undervalued rupiah offered ample room for further appreciation against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  In its latest "Indonesian Rupiah" report made available on Thursday to The Jakarta Post MWD said that at the current level of 6,800 to the U.S. dollar, the rupiah was still grossly undervalued. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah is 25 percent undervalued. This implies that the dollar-rupiah could in principle fall to the 5,000 to 5,500 range," MWD said. \par \par \uc2  The report implied that the current rupiah value continued, to some extent, to be dictated by decisions made during the previous administration under former president B.J. Habibie, who often had awkward relations with the international aid institutions. \par \par \uc2  After two years of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) democratically elected last week the country's President and Vice President for the first time in its history. \par \par \uc2  "The significance of a legitimate government in Indonesia should not be underestimated," the report said. \par \par \uc2  The report added that the composition of the Cabinet formed this week by newly elected president Abdurrahman Wahid had made an important step in further establishing his government's legitimacy. \par \par \uc2  "(The Cabinet) is free of blatant ethnic, political and religious biases or alliances," the report said. \par \par \uc2  The report stated that the positive political developments of the last nine days played a tremendous part in reducing the political risk status of the country. \par \par \uc2  "Essentially, the biggest noneconomic risks are now behind us. From this point forward, the dollar-rupiah will be determined more by \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals than the noneconomic factors." \par \par \uc2  The report also acknowledged the substantial problems Indonesia was facing, such as solving the external debt overhang, completing the domestic bank restructuring program and creating a conducive environment to attract foreign direct investment. \par \par \uc2  "However, with the new government in place, the international creditors would be more inclined to consider debt rescheduling and write-offs," the report said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed lower at 6,925 against the greenback on Thursday, compared to 6,910 the previous day. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said that the trading volume was meager due to the lack of fresh leads on the new government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  direction. \par \par \uc2  "We are closely monitoring what programs the newly formed Cabinet will implement, and also hoping for the prompt release of the full report on the Bank Bali case by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," one dealer said. \par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Stock Exchange Composite Index ended higher by 1.4 points, or a quarter percent, to 577.93, with the volume of 255 million shares valued at Rp 411 billion. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said a late buying spree on select blue chips prevented the index from closing lower on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  They said investors were cautious during the day over whether the new Cabinet would prove capable to cope with the country's crisis-hit \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (udi) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dvat006fx\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Indosat delays divestment to September 2000. \b0\par\par\uc2 483 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 November 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  PT Indosat Tbk is again to delay its divestment plan to strategic investors until the new telecommunications bill No. 36/1999 is effective September next year. \par \par \uc2  President Director of PT Indosat Tbk Indra Setiawan said the privatization process of the state firm is temporarily delayed as the telecommunications regulations are still in the transition period. \par \par \uc2  "Apart from that, the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation is not favorable for us to divest the shares to strategic investors," he told Bisnis in the sideline of a hand-over ceremony of the ministerial post at the Transportation Ministry over the weekend. \par \par \uc2  Indosat is currently concentrating on mapping out its affiliates so that the state firm can concentrate on the core businesses that could contribute good performance in the future. \par \par \uc2  "First of all, I have to look at the company subsidiaries one by one. I am now studying the multimedia companies, that's why the privatization is delayed. But this of course depends on the new minister that handles the state firms," he said. \par \par \uc2  Previously the government also delayed Indosat's divestment as it awaited for the new telecommunications law. Three foreign investors who was interested in the private placement were British Telecom, France Telecom and Telstra Australia. \par \par \uc2  A Bisnis source at the Transportation Ministry said foreign investors are taking a wait and see stance before deciding to invest in Indonesia as they are not quite clear with the telecommunications law and the blue print although they have already been issued. \par \par \uc2  They are even more reluctant with the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of whether it is necessary for the government to speed up the annulment of Telkom and Indosat exclusive rights. \par \par \uc2  "If the government speeds up the nullification of the exclusive rights, this will affect the shares of Indosat and Telkom. So it is natural if they wait for the government's regulations," said the source and added that investors want to see a more open telecommunications sector. \par \par \uc2  "Foreign investors want the government to provide more details on the \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the new regulations. We have already explained to them that the tariffs will be made in a separate \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but they are not satisfied with that," he said. \par \par \uc2  A score of strategic investors had shown their interests during the due diligence process, they were AT&T, KDD and NTT Japan, PTT Netherland and Cables & Wireless LLC, and the three other mentioned earlier. \par \par \uc2  Last year, Indosat saw a net profit of around Rp1.1 trillion or up 71.7% compared to 1997. In the first semester of this year, Indosat booked a net revenue of Rp683.4 billion or up by 36.8% compared to the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  The company's operation revenue was Rp1,385.7 billion, up 36.4% compared to the same period in the year before which stood at Rp1,015.7 billion. (sup). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dvb1000h7\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'Stop state  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  leakage'. \b0\par\par\uc2 332 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 November 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Economist Sri Adiningsih urged the government to put a halt on leakage in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN) as an effort to foresee the possibility of no foreign loan disbursement. \par \par \uc2  Sri said the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  might face problems as loans from the IMF and the World Bank have not been disbursed, while revenue from oil, gas and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  is \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and weak. \par \par \uc2  "If the government can in the next 100 days prevent APBN leakage by 30%, that means that it has an additional income of 30%," she said. \par \par \uc2  "I believe Finance Minister Bambang Sudibyo can set the priorities by postponing unnecessary projects," Sri Adiningsih said on Jakarta News FM-Metro Live Discussion here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Economist Tjiptono Darmadji added that if the government wishes to boost \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue, the real sector must be allowed to move again. \par \par \uc2  "As such, bank recapitalization must be expedited," she said. \par \par \uc2  He said the government should lessen its dependence on IMF by boosting national saving. \par \par \uc2  Senior \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister Kwik Kian Gie and Bambang Sudibyo last week differed on their views over the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  According to the finance minister, there is a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  surplus of Rp17 trillion up to December, while the senior minister, quoting dailies' reports, said the nation suffers from a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  On the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team, Sri Adiningsih said it all depends on the inflation, the exchange rate of the rupiah and the balance of payment in the next three months. \par \par \uc2  She said one couldn't expect the team to improve the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  significantly in the next 100 days "as the problems are so complex." \par \par \uc2  Tjiptono Darmadji has set seven factors with which to evaluate the team's level of success. \par \par \uc2  They are namely low inflation, the rupiah at 6,500/US$, the JSX index at over 650, half of the companies listed at the BPPN succeed in restructuring their debts, bank recapitalization finalized, loan \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  at below 20% and positive non-oil/gas exports. (ab). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dvb2000hd\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
