\par\par \b \uc2  IBRA may delay BCA share issue till March. \b0\par\par\uc2 674 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 January 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) may have to delay the crucial initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering (IPO) plans of Bank Central Asia (BCA) until March because the agency has been slow in registering the plans at the country's Capital Market Supervisory Agency (Bapepam). \par \par \uc2  Head of IBRA's asset management and investment team Dasa Sutanto confirmed on Sunday that the agency had not yet registered the IPO plans. \par \par \uc2  "We'll do it first thing next week (this week)," he told The Jakarta Post by phone. \par \par \uc2  The BCA IPO was set for February. But according to a Bapepam ruling, an IPO plan must be registered at the capital market watchdog 45 days before the primary offering is made. \par \par \uc2  Dasa said the February schedule was an IBRA internal target to push its staff to work harder to realize the BCA IPO so that it could meet the government's target of raising some Rp 17 trillion (US$2.3 billion) in cash in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year ending on March 31. \par \par \uc2  He was confident the IPO could go through in March, while saying the BCA IPO was crucial to restoring investors' confidence in the country's ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  IBRA has said it plans to raise Rp 3 trillion in proceeds from the BCA IPO by selling a 30 percent stake. \par \par \uc2  But Dasa said the agency could sell less than 30 percent if there was a strong market demand for the BCA offering. \par \par \uc2  Asked why IBRA had been slow in making the registration at Bapepam, Dasa said the agency had to focus first on improving BCA's credit supervision department, which had been one of the bank's greatest weaknesses. \par \par \uc2  He said a foreign bank had been assigned to do the job. \par \par \uc2  "We wanted to make sure everything was okay before we launched the bank on the market," he said. \par \par \uc2  IBRA, a unit of the finance ministry, took over BCA in 1998 after its owners, the Salim Group and two children of former president Soeharto, failed to repay the bank's debts to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  BCA, the country's largest private bank, has total assets of some Rp 84.4 trillion and operates some 767 branches throughout the country. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has appointed Lehman Brothers, Merrill Lynch and local securities firms PT Bahana Securities and PT Danareksa Securities to manage the BCA IPO. \par \par \uc2  The agency controls some Rp 600 trillion worth of various banking assets. It is mandated to sell or recover the assets to raise cash to help finance the government's costly bank restructuring and recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  In the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, IBRA must raise Rp 17 trillion to help finance the Rp 34 trillion interest cost of the bank restructuring and recapitalization bonds issued by the government. \par \par \uc2  IBRA is targeted to raise some Rp 16 trillion in cash in the coming \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has said it had so far raised more than Rp 10 trillion in cash and is confident that it could meet the Rp 17 trillion target. \par \par \uc2  The BCA IPO and the plans to sell its 40 percent ownership in the publicly listed auto giant PT Astra International would be the major contributor to fulfilling that target. \par \par \uc2  But the planned sale of Astra seemed to fall into \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  after IBRA was reportedly in a spat with Astra's Rini Soewandi-led management team. \par \par \uc2  The agency has indicated that it is proposing to dismiss Astra's current management team at an upcoming Feb. 8 extraordinary shareholders meeting. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has accused the management team of obstructing the planned sale of its equity shares in the company to an American investor consortium led by Newbridge Capital and Gilbert Global Equity. \par \par \uc2  However, the management denied all the allegations, arguing that it wanted only to ensure that all securities market regulations and good corporate governance practices were fully observed in the transaction. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, a "respected blue chip financial investor" has reportedly offered a better price for IBRA's stake in Astra. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw1o00b5g\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
