\par\par \b \uc2  FRIDAY'S EDITORIALS IN MAJOR INDONESIAN DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 1,235 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 February 2000\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  - THAT ROADSHOW AND ITS TEDIOUS STATEMENTS \par \par \uc2  In the words of Aburizal Bakrie, president of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (KADIN), President Abdurrahman Wahid has managed to convince leaders of several countries in Europe that conditions in Indonesia have returned to normal. \par \par \uc2  Perhaps Bakrie was trying to take some of the dreariness out of this safari - the third one on a few months - when he said there that foreign countries are beginning to admit that there has been some improvement in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  As president of the KADIN, he probably felt obliged to say such things - which are also a repetition of the same things he said when he accompanied former president Soeharto to South Africa. \par \par \uc2  Things will only improve in this country, and investors will only invest their money here, if and when the supremacy of the law prevails. It's as simple as that. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  - WE'RE PLEASED BEING TRUSTED, BUT CONCERNED OVER RISING DEBTS \par \par \uc2  Once again, the international community's support for Indonesia is proven \par \par \uc2  despite the fact that we are still gripped by \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Regardless of the various interests that go along with the support, the \par \par \uc2  Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI)'s new commitment to lending the country US$4.7 billion to close \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will help us do whatever has been planned for this year. \par \par \uc2  However, we are also concerned because of the debt of ours which has reached US$150 billion, including that of the private sector, which has made us and our grand children be heavier to bear the debt burden because the due time of the total loan will fall in 20 to 30 years ahead. \par \par \uc2  It is not easy for us to increase our domestic income by maximally making an effort to make our people bear no much more burden, but it is the best choice for us because in one hand, it is no longer easy to get soft loan, while on the other hand, we also do not want to keep on relying on other parties. \par \par \uc2  When we fall, it seems that we like following whatever the donor countries want and order. Isn't it part of the things that make some of us not happy with the presence of the International Monetary Fund here? - Kompas \par \par \uc2  - PRESERVING OUR HONOR \par \par \uc2  It would seem that the United Nations will reject an international court as \par \par \uc2  an appropriate forum for the proposed trials relating to the East Timor massacres, and instead wants Indonesia to conduct its own trials here in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Psychologically, this is a very important question for Indonesia because by allowing Indonesia to hold the trials on its own, the UN will help Indonesia preserve its honor and reputation in the eyes of the international world. \par \par \uc2  In the meantime, several countries have let it be known that if Indonesia is given the chance to conduct the trial, it is doomed to failure and that a miscarriage of justice may take place. \par \par \uc2  We believe that such assumptions are premature and without foundation in light of the report submitted by the Investigative Commission on Human Rights Abuses in East Timor, the National Commission on Human Rights and the Office of the Attorney General. \par \par \uc2  Other people should not get too worried about the whole affairs because we are quite capable of keeping this within the limits of reasonability. This will also mean that everybody can get a fair trial. \par \par \uc2  The only person who seems to have lost his cool here is our president. It would be nice if his foreign minister, Alwi Shihab, could make him understand that he should stop this show of bad taste at once. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  - A WAR AGAINST DRUG \par \par \uc2  Bitterly, we have to be willing enough in earning a bad title as a fertile \par \par \uc2  land for distributing drugs. A story of drug is now owned by everybody: the \par \par \uc2  simple and the haves; those in the village and in the city. \par \par \uc2  Quoting a word made by an organisation, there is only one word: Fight \par \par \uc2  against it, but it should be a total one. \par \par \uc2  Thus, we hail -- with a big-hope -- the House which is now discussing the \par \par \uc2  law on drugs to revise the old one which has been proved to be failed in \par \par \uc2  bringing the drug dealers and users to court. \par \par \uc2  But the new law would be nothing if the law would still choose their \par \par \uc2  "patients". And if the apparatus would still be "behind" the practice. \par \par \uc2  Thus, the drug case involving a son of a former military officer should \par \par \uc2  initiate all the legal process against the drug abuse. If not, the people will \par \par \uc2  loose trust to any government's good-will in fighting against the drug. \par \par \uc2  And, it could be imagined in our eyes that this nation will experience life \par \par \uc2  sadly. -- Media Indonesia \par \par \uc2  - WANTED: A GOOD JUDGE \par \par \uc2  Was President Abdurrahman Wahid wrong in proposing Benjamin Mangkoedilaga as \par \par \uc2  chief justice ? Constitutionally, the President does not have the right to meddle in the judicial body. The prerogative to nominate members of the Supreme Court, including its chief, belongs to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The president, therefore, has overstepped his authority when he suggested that Benjamin, a former judge whose commitment to democracy and justice a beyond doubt, take over from Chief Justice Sarwata when the latter reaches the mandatory retirement age of 65 in August. \par \par \uc2  While the President is as committed to upholding the law as the next person, the law requiring the chief justice be selected from existing justice must be waived, should none of them meet the criteria and demands of the time. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid may not have the authority to nominate the next chief justice, but he definitely spoke for many people in this country when he proposed Benjamin for the job. The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , whose task it is to nominate the candidates should heed the wishes of the people. Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  -  WIRANTO'S FATE \par \par \uc2  All ministers' fate depends on the president. Whatever the President's \par \par \uc2  decision is, as long as it is made in accordance with existing procedures, it \par \par \uc2  must be obeyed. Otherwise, it is a disobedience. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid was reported to have ordered Defence Minister, \par \par \uc2  Juwono Sudarsono, to ask Coordinating Minister for Political and Security \par \par \uc2  Affairs, General Wiranto to resign. \par \par \uc2  Why the president does not directly ask Wiranto to resign from his position \par \par \uc2  despite the fact that the President has prerogative right to appoint and replace \par \par \uc2  his aides? \par \par \uc2  What the president did to Wiranto is not only "replacing the minister" based \par \par \uc2  on the international dimension of the alleged involvement of some generals and other high ranking officers of Indonesian Defence Force (TNI) in East Timor's atrocities, but he seemed to have confidence that military fully supports him. \par \par \uc2  Maybe, his all moves are expected to promote his prestige in the eyes of the international community due to his seriousness in handling problems which have been the international concern. \par \par \uc2  The problem is that it is not an appropriate move if such a decision is made in a hurry to get a target. - Republika. \par \par \uc2  (c) 2000 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. \par \par \uc2  Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dw24002pk\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
