\par\par \b \uc2  BI to adopt tight  \highlight22\uc2 policy \highlight\uc2  to arrest fall of rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 477 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 February 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  will adopt a tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in a bid to arrest the fall of the flagging rupiah against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom said here on Thursday that a tighter \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was unavoidable after the United States increased its \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We have to do something or the market will punish us," she told reporters on the sidelines of a seminar. \par \par \uc2  But she added that it is too early to say whether the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would immediately increase its benchmark interest rate. \par \par \uc2  She said, however, that the monetary tightening \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would definitely slow the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's intention to cut the interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's (SBI) promissory note to the 10 percent level. \par \par \uc2  "The hike in U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would slow down the decline in the SBI rates. So it will not happen as quickly as expected," she said. \par \par \uc2  The interest rate of the one-month SBI note is currently at 11.04 percent, compared to the record level of 70 percent in the middle of 1998 when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis deepened, and around 35 percent in early 1999. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been under pressure to ensure that domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  go as low as possible to minimize the interest costs of government bonds issued to finance the country's bank restructuring and recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2   , The U.S. Federal Reserve on Wednesday raised its main interest rate by a quarter point to 5.75 percent in a bid to cool down the overheating \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The Fed also indicated that it would increase rates further. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the hike in U.S. rates had contributed to the overall decline in world currencies against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  "All currencies in the world including the yen, Australian dollar, Singapore dollar and the rupiah are under pressure," she said. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that another factor affecting the rupiah was the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by the dispute between President Abdurrahman Wahid and former armed forces commander Gen. Wiranto, who is now the Coordinating Minister for Security and Political Affairs. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman said earlier this week that Wiranto should resign to allow a fair investigation of his alleged involvement in the human rights violations in the former East Timor. Abdurrahman made the statement following rumors that a certain section of the military was planning a coup. Wiranto has rejected the calls for his resignation. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah started the week at around Rp 7,400 per U.S. dollar, and has closed at Rp 7,660, down from Rp 7,520. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by the political infighting between Abdurrahman and Wiranto has discouraged foreign investors from entering the country. \par \par \uc2  "Investors are still adopting a wait and see attitude," she said. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw24009dn\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BI set to raise  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 599 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 February 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) deputy governor Miranda Swaray Goeltom has indicated here yesterday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  might raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the rupiah continues to weaken against the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said the weak rupiah is due to domestic and foreign rumors. \par \par \uc2  She is optimistic that the rupiah would again strengthen in the near future. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said investors have short-, medium-and long-term perspectives. \par \par \uc2  "If this week sees rates rising by one or two basis points, that is seen as normal. This is also due to The Fed's plan to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  In the FOMC meeting on Wednesday, the Fed raised Fed Fund by 25 basis points to 5.75% from 5.50%, while discounted rates have been raised from 5.25% to 5.50%. \par \par \uc2  At the same time, Miranda added, the European \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  shows little promise. As a result, the euro fell to 0,97, the Australian $0.63, the New Zealand $1.71 against the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  "So many major currencies have fallen against the US dollar," she said. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said General Wiranto has become part of the country's political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Although accusations against Wiranto may mot be true, investors prefer to take a wait and see stance. \par \par \uc2  "This puts pressure on the rupiah." \par \par \uc2  She said BI would raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  "only if it is necessary" as the aggregate monetary development of BI is "very good." \par \par \uc2  Based money in December 1999 was very high at Rp101 trillion due to Y2K rumors. \par \par \uc2  But after it was over, it reached normal levels at Rp86 trillion. \par \par \uc2  "This leads to expectation that \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would fall." \par \par \uc2  Economist of Bahana Sekuritas, Budi Hikmat, said he could understand BI's plans as the rupiah has reached 7,600 against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  "BI's move is also meant to rein in inflation." \par \par \uc2  "BI must however be careful not to send the wrong signals, as rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would have a negative impact." \par \par \uc2  First, it would disrupt monetary diversification in the capital and bond markets, as market players would re-calculate their investment. \par \par \uc2  Second, the cost of bank recapitalization would rise. \par \par \uc2  Dow Jones data show that the rupiah dropped by 86 points (1.12%) to 7,676 from 7,590 on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The US dollar range against the rupiah is 6,650 and 7,700. \par \par \uc2  In the international market (21.00 WIB) the rupiah moved at the 7,650 level. \par \par \uc2  House member Theo Toemion predicted that the US dollar would hit the 8,000 level if the political situation remains unstable and BI does nothing about it. \par \par \uc2  "In a slow market, prices of basic needs could rise in a development that is unrelated to the dollar. This could be a big problem for the new government." \par \par \uc2  If the status of Wiranto remains unclear, this could prolong the poor situation, "while President Gus Dur is still a long way from arriving back home." \par \par \uc2  Theo blamed BI for allowing the rupiah to drop to the 7,000 level because "BI, with its large funds, could have influenced the market." \par \par \uc2  "I'm concerned over foreign reaction to the presence of a strong man in Indonesia defying the President. This causes fear in the market," he said. \par \par \uc2  Investors, said Theo, are now divesting shares to buy dollars since the East Timor inquiry made \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  its findings. \par \par \uc2  "We still recall the fall of Soeharto because of the fall of the rupiah. The government could be successful in diplomacy and policies. But one must also look at the continuing fall of the rupiah." (m6/yn/dj/jao). \par \par \uc2  (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dw2400056\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
