\par\par \b \uc2  MONDAY'S EDITORIALS IN MAJOR INDONESIAN DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 1,088 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 February 2000\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  - READING THE PRESIDENT \par \par \uc2  Whatever the limitations of the office, there can be no question that the president of the Republic of Indonesia is a powerful man. He is not only the country's head of government, but also its head of state. \par \par \uc2  It is understandable that there is currently much criticism of President Abdurrahman Wahid - or, to be more precise, of his unceremonious, easy-going style of governing - in this time of crisis. His penchant for making seemingly ambiguous statements about all kinds of issues, from the most immaterial to the most serious, has of late particularly come under fire. \par \par \uc2  In a country that has only just been liberated from over three decades of authoritarian rule and where timeworn traditions are still cherished, many people obviously are finding it difficult to adjust to having such a relaxed President at the helm during these difficult times. \par \par \uc2  Ever since his election as President of the republic in October last year, Abdurrahman - though unquestionably bright and perceptive, and evidently loved and respected by many ordinary Indonesian - has shown a talent for stepping on people's toes. \par \par \uc2  Parliamentarians, political analysts and leaders have called on the President to rein in his penchant for making rash statements and bring a little more dignity to the office of the presidency. \par \par \uc2  However, unless time proves us wrong we believe Indonesians would do best to get used to this peculiar style of leadership which, after all, is and always has been uniquely Abdurrahman's. \par \par \uc2  Indonesians, after all, need to free themselves from the notion that the president is someone remote and powerful, who must be feared and at all times obeyed. At the very least, even in the brief time he has been in office, Abdurrahman has succeeded in helping Indonesians shed much of their excessive deference to power.-The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  - BE CAREFUL MR.PRESIDENT! \par \par \uc2  Is it true that there will be coup d'etat by the Indonesian \par \par \uc2  military (TNI) to topple President Abdurrahman Wahid's administration? This question is still circulated in society until now despite the fact that TNI Commander Admiral Widodo AS has once told news conference in Jakarta that there is no effort to topple the legitimate government. "Do they not refer to history?" he was quoted by media as asking. \par \par \uc2  However, none knows why President Wahid always touches this matter during his overseas trip. Let us forget all groundless indications of the head of state. Let us assume that it is quite impossible for the state intelligence unit to give the baseless inputs to the president. \par \par \uc2  He actually wants to use his overseas trip as a momentum to strengthen his political position in domestic and international fora. Who knows, sometime in the future, there will be efforts of certain TNI groups or others to oust him from power, then his government remains recognised by international community. \par \par \uc2  Such a strategy is still our prediction. Isn't he very smart to make a strategy as he had shown as in a away to be appointed the president in October. But, in return, all statements on the TNI coup and meeting of the generals at Lautze street might only be mistakes. \par \par \uc2  These all can happen because the president's habit is always doing improvisation. It means his statement can be right or wrong. If it is true, his administration will save, but if not, he supposes that it is only a human error ... \par \par \uc2  But, it must be kept in mind that if the habit of making \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  rumours has been a president's habit, we must take pity on the people because they will be affected and suspect to one another. They think that their fate is \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . What will the country be? So, be careful Mr.President! - Republika \par \par \uc2  - RECONCILIATION OF \b \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC\b0 \highlight\uc2  POLICIES \par \par \uc2  The 2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft unexpectedly received strong \par \par \uc2  reactions from economist. They felt pessimistic and confused if the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is connected to the efforts of transparency, decreasing foreign debt, \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  accountability and deconcentration of \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the central to regional government. \par \par \uc2  The direction of reconciliation of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies that are expected to emerge in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is in fact far away from the target. There is no joint spirit between \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers and the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (\b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) governor. \par \par \uc2  Research, conducted by the Development of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Financial Institution (Indef) in Jakarta disclosed that the development strategy of people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as clearly revealed in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 1999-2004, is not given full attention. \par \par \uc2  The reconciliation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sect